<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,762,787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet comes from Spanish (“pa” = “dad”), in honor of William Galvis Peñuela, good friend and author’s father, for his friendship, guidance, help, and continued support during the author’s studies and research on Neotropical and Colombian salticids, and main financial supporter of the author’s long collecting trips, including some of this research.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,906,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[435,508,907,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[435,508,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. pae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,605,906,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[515,605,906,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[867,1014,907,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tisquesusa" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[867,1014,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. tisquesusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1022,1107,906,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1022,1107,906,931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">sp. nov</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shape of the RTA and the absence of the basal widening of the embolus. However, they can be distinguished from those by the shorter and wider RTA, a slenderer tegular lobe (TL), and a longer embolus (
<figureCitation box="[926,1040,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[207,1418,446,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[177,1421,409,1893]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 7 a – d. A. pae sp. nov., a) left male palp, ventral view; b) same, retroventral view. A. quimbaya sp. nov., c) left male palp, ventral view; d) same, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: DTS = dorsal tibial spur, e = embolus, ED = embolic disc, EF = embolic filament, PED = process on embolic disc, RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp, SD = sperm duct, TL = tegular lobe. Scale bars: 0.30 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828220/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 7a–b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1124,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[187,1405,208,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 21 a – k. Amphidraus spp, left male palp. A. guatavita sp. nov., a) ventral view; b) same, retrolateral view; c) same, dorsal view of the tibia. A. pae sp. nov., d) ventral view; e) same, retrolateral view. A. quimbaya sp. nov., f) ventral view; g) same, retrolateral view. A. quinini sp. nov., h) ventral view, partially expanded; i) same, retrolateral view. A. sie sp. nov., j) ventral view; k) same, retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828248/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">21d–e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,559,1014,1039]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus box="[439,547,1014,1039]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Total length: 3.07. Carapace dark brown with a lighter mark behind the thoracic groove and a transversal cuticular metallic-blue mark, 1.60 long, 1.10 wide, 0.87 high (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1374,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 17" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1660,1682]" captionTargetBox="[340,1244,413,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[340,1247,411,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 17 a – i. A. guatavita sp. nov., a) male holotype (ANDES – IN 3155). A. pae sp. nov., b) male holotype (ICN – Ar 6576). A. quimbaya sp. nov., c) male holotype (ICN – Ar 7746). A. quinini sp. nov., d) male holotype (ICN – Ar 8266); e) female paratype (ICN – Ar 8267). A. sie sp. nov., f) male holotype (ICN – Ar 8254); g) female paratype (ICN – Ar 8255). A. sikuani sp. nov., h) male holotype (ICN – Ar 6558); i) female paratype (ICN – Ar 7185). Scale bars: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828240/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 17b</figureCitation>
). OC black 0.66 long. Anterior eye row 1.13 wide and posterior 0.97 wide. Sternum dark brown, 0.55 long, 0.46 wide. Labium dark brown, 0.12 long, 0.16 wide. Chelicerae dark brown with four retromarginal and two promarginal teeth. Palp dark brown with femur and patella with white hairs, a visible prolateral sperm duct (SD), and a single finger-like RTA (
<figureCitation box="[345,460,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[207,1418,446,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[177,1421,409,1893]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 7 a – d. A. pae sp. nov., a) left male palp, ventral view; b) same, retroventral view. A. quimbaya sp. nov., c) left male palp, ventral view; d) same, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: DTS = dorsal tibial spur, e = embolus, ED = embolic disc, EF = embolic filament, PED = process on embolic disc, RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp, SD = sperm duct, TL = tegular lobe. Scale bars: 0.30 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828220/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 7a–b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[473,545,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1917,1939]" captionTargetBox="[187,1405,208,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 21 a – k. Amphidraus spp, left male palp. A. guatavita sp. nov., a) ventral view; b) same, retrolateral view; c) same, dorsal view of the tibia. A. pae sp. nov., d) ventral view; e) same, retrolateral view. A. quimbaya sp. nov., f) ventral view; g) same, retrolateral view. A. quinini sp. nov., h) ventral view, partially expanded; i) same, retrolateral view. A. sie sp. nov., j) ventral view; k) same, retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828248/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">21d–e</figureCitation>
). Legs 1432, leg I dark brown, legs II–IV yellow with dark brown marks. Leg macrosetae: femur, I d 1 di; II d 1 di, p 1 di; III–IV d 2 di, p 1 di; patella, III–IV r 1 me; tibia, I 
<date box="[1224,1285,1231,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 2-2</date>
-2; II 
<date box="[1347,1405,1231,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 1-2</date>
-2, p 1 di; III 
<date box="[263,323,1267,1291]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 1-2</date>
, p 1 me, r 1 me; IV 
<date box="[546,605,1267,1291]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 1-1</date>
, p 1-1, r 1 di; metatarsus, I 
<date box="[913,974,1267,1291]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 2-2</date>
; II 
<date box="[1011,1070,1267,1291]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 2-2</date>
, p 1 di; III 
<date box="[1195,1255,1267,1291]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 2-2</date>
, p 1-2, r 1-2; IV 
<date box="[151,212,1303,1327]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">v 1-2</date>
, p 1-1-2, r 1-1-2. Abdomen light brown with dark brown marks and a medial transversal dark brown stripe (
<figureCitation box="[159,257,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 17" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1660,1682]" captionTargetBox="[340,1244,413,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[340,1247,411,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 17 a – i. A. guatavita sp. nov., a) male holotype (ANDES – IN 3155). A. pae sp. nov., b) male holotype (ICN – Ar 6576). A. quimbaya sp. nov., c) male holotype (ICN – Ar 7746). A. quinini sp. nov., d) male holotype (ICN – Ar 8266); e) female paratype (ICN – Ar 8267). A. sie sp. nov., f) male holotype (ICN – Ar 8254); g) female paratype (ICN – Ar 8255). A. sikuani sp. nov., h) male holotype (ICN – Ar 6558); i) female paratype (ICN – Ar 7185). Scale bars: 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/828240/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 17b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,690,1435]" box="[199,418,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
